Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Bot
    The bot has a hand and four unique play card methods based on the number of cards in the current middle pile.
    Card
    The card class creates a card object that contains a suit, a number, and a image that corresponds to that suit and number.
    CardButton
    This class extends JButton in order to include a Card object to each button, making it easier to see what card is being played based on the button pressed in the GUI.
    Deck
    Deck is 52 unique card objects, 13 in each of clubs, spades hearts, and diamonds (no duplicates).
    Driver
    Driver helps run the game, but the primary running of the game takes place in GUI.
    GUI  
    Hand
    Hand is a list of 13 card objects, used by any human or bot, it contains methods to check the status and manipulate the cards in the hand.
    Human
    Human is a player, it has a name and a hand and plays the game of spades based on user clicks through the GUI.
    Memory
    Memory is used by the Bot.
    Player
    Player is extended by both bot and human.
    RulesWindow
    This class defines the Rules Window GUI that is displayed upon clicking the "How to Play" button on the Welcome GUI.
    Spades
    This is the game executer, it calls the welcome GUI, which starts the whole game.
    WelcomeGUI
    This class defines the Welcome GUI that is displayed when the program is first launched.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Suit
    The enumerated type suit for each card in the card class.
